      "text": "Contents of https://luyaojie.github.io/:\n|  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| |  |  | | --- | --- | | [Chinese Information Processing Laboratory](http://www.icip.org.cn/) | | | [Institute of Software, Chinese Academy of Sciences](http://www.iscas.ac.cn/) | | | Room 1201, 4#\xa0 South\xa0 Fourth Street, Zhong Guan Cun  Haidian District, Beijing | | |  | | | Email: luyaojie{at}iscas{dot}ac{dot}cn | |  | | |  | |  |\n\n### Short Bio\n\nI am an Associate Professor at the [Chinese Information Processing Laboratory](http://www.icip.org.cn/), [Institute of Software](http://www.iscas.ac.cn/), [Chinese Academy of Sciences](https://www.cas.cn/).\n\n### Research Interests\n\nMy research interests center on **Natural Language Processing**, such as Information\nExtraction and Large Language Models.\n\n### Selected Publications ([Full List](https://dblp.org/pid/15/3214-1.html))\n\n* Rethinking Reward Model Evaluation: Are We Barking up the Wrong Tree?\n  Xueru Wen, Jie Lou, **Yaojie Lu**, Hongyu Lin, XingYu, Xinyu Lu, Ben He, Xianpei Han, Debing Zhang, Le Sun.\n  ICLR 2025.\n  [[link](https://openreview.net/pdf?id=Cnwz9jONi5)]\n* SoFA: Shielded On-the-fly Alignment via Priority Rule Following.\n  Xinyu Lu, Bowen Yu, **Yaojie Lu**, Hongyu Lin, Haiyang Yu, Le Sun, Xianpei Han, Yongbin Li.\n  ACL Findings 2024.\n  [[link](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2402.17358)]\n* Mitigating Large Language Model Hallucinations via Autonomous Knowledge Graph-Based Retrofitting.\n  Xinyan Guan, Yanjiang Liu, Hongyu Lin, **Yaojie Lu**, Ben He, Xianpei Han, Le Sun.\n  AAAI 2024.\n  [[link](https://ojs.aaai.org/index.php/AAAI/article/view/29770/)]\n* Learning In-context Learning for Named Entity Recognition.\n  Jiawei Chen, **Yaojie Lu**, Hongyu Lin, Jie Lou, Wei Jia, Dai Dai, Hua Wu, Boxi Cao, Xianpei Han, Le Sun.\n  ACL 2023.\n  [[link](https://aclanthology.org/2023.acl-long.764/)]\n* Unified Structure Generation for Universal Information Extraction.\n  **Yaojie Lu**, Qing Liu, Dai Dai, Xinyan Xiao, Hongyu Lin, Xianpei Han, Le Sun and Hua Wu.\n  ACL 2022.\n  [[link](https://aclanthology.org/2022.acl-long.395/)]\n* Text2Event: Controllable Sequence-to-Structure Generation for End-to-end Event Extraction.\n  **Yaojie Lu**, Hongyu Lin, Jin Xu, Xianpei Han, Jialong Tang, Annan Li, Le Sun, Meng Liao and Shaoyi Chen.\n  ACL-IJCNLP 2021.\n  [[link](https://aclanthology.org/2021.acl-long.217/)]\n\n### Useful Resources\n\n#### Repositories I Maintain\n\n[[Awesome Resource for NLP](https://github.com/luyaojie/awesome-nlp-resource)]\nSome useful datasets for NLP.\n  \n[[NLP Resource in Chinese Conference](https://github.com/luyaojie/chinese-nlp-conference-resource)]\nSome useful resources for NLP (in Chinese).  \n\n#### Conferences Info\n\n[AI Conference Deadlines](https://aideadlin.es/)  \n[WikiCFP](http://www.wikicfp.com/cfp)  \n\n\n### Professional Activities\n\nProgram Committee Members:\nACL (ARR),\nNeurIPS,\nICLR,\nAAAI,\nIJCAI,\nEMNLP,\nCOLM,\nCOLING,\nCCL,\nCCKS.\n  \n\n\n---\n\nLast updated: April 2, 2025",
