      "text": "Contents of https://www.bbc.com/news/business:\n[Skip to content](#main-content)\n\n[British Broadcasting Corporation](/)\n\n* [Home](/)\n* [News](/news)\n* [Sport](/sport)\n* [Business](/business)\n* [Innovation](/innovation)\n* [Culture](/culture)\n* [Arts](/arts)\n* [Travel](/travel)\n* [Earth](/future-planet)\n* [Audio](/audio)\n* [Video](/video)\n* [Live](/live)\n\n* [Executive Lounge](/business/executive-lounge)\n* [Technology of Business](/business/technology-of-business)\n* [Future of Business](/business/future-of-business)\n\n[![](https://static.files.bbci.co.uk/bbcdotcom/web/20250711-084946-a521911844-web-2.25.0-9/grey-placeholder.png)![Taylor Swift performs onstage during The Eras Tour show at Lucas Oil Stadium on November 01, 2024 in Indianapolis, Indiana. Dressed in a pink sparkly dress, she is standing on stage in front of a pink mist, with a purple microphone in her hand. ](https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/7804/live/8fdcc660-669b-11f0-8848-6933f9c7a3ff.jpg.webp)\n\n## Taylor Swift and Drake music giant files to list on US stock market\n\nIt comes as two major US share indexes closed at new record highs on Monday.\n\n5 hrs ago\n\nBusiness](/news/articles/ce9xlmpz129o)\n\n[![](https://static.files.bbci.co.uk/bbcdotcom/web/20250711-084946-a521911844-web-2.25.0-9/grey-placeholder.png)![A red graduation cap on the head of a graduate with long brown hair, pictured from the back. On the cap is printed \"Harvard 2025\" and \"Learn to change the world\". Other graduates with red gowns can be seen blurred in the background](https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/16b5/live/6211f810-6635-11f0-9b46-d5bea8d921ec.jpg.webp)\n\n## Harvard and Trump lawyers clash in court over funding fight\n\nThe top university is suing over the administration's decision to cut funds due to claims of antisemitism on campus.\n\n8 hrs ago\n\nUS & Canada](/news/articles/cj9vkve298no)\n\n[![](https://static.files.bbci.co.uk/bbcdotcom/web/20250711-084946-a521911844-web-2.25.0-9/grey-placeholder.png)![World of Business](https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/raw/p0jq6tfl.jpg.webp)\n\n## World of Business\n\nGain the leading edge with global insights for the boardroom and beyond, in your inbox every Wednesday.](https://cloud.email.bbc.com/WorldofBusiness_Newsletter_Signup?&at_bbc_team=studios&at_medium=emails&at_objective=acquisition&at_ptr_type=&at_ptr_name=bbc.com&at_format=Module&at_link_origin=homepage&at_campaign=wob&at_campaign_type=owned)\n\n[## Ryanair mulls bigger bonus for spotting oversized bags\n\nThe airline says it is \"determined to eliminate the scourge of oversized bags\" on its planes.\n\n13 hrs ago\n\nBusiness](/news/articles/c75rp3w77kpo)\n\n[## Weak password allowed hackers to sink a 158-year-old company\n\nTransport company KNP forced to shut down after international hacker gangs target thousands of UK businesses.\n\n1 day ago\n\nTechnology](/news/articles/cx2gx28815wo)\n\n[![](https://static.files.bbci.co.uk/bbcdotcom/web/20250711-084946-a521911844-web-2.25.0-9/grey-placeholder.png)![A red graduation cap on the head of a graduate with long brown hair, pictured from the back. On the cap is printed \"Harvard 2025\" and \"Learn to change the world\". Other graduates with red gowns can be seen blurred in the background](https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/16b5/live/6211f810-6635-11f0-9b46-d5bea8d921ec.jpg.webp)\n\n## Harvard and Trump lawyers clash in court over funding fight\n\nThe top university is suing over the administration's decision to cut funds due to claims of antisemitism on campus.\n\n8 hrs ago\n\nUS & Canada](/news/articles/cj9vkve298no)\n\n[![](https://static.files.bbci.co.uk/bbcdotcom/web/20250711-084946-a521911844-web-2.25.0-9/grey-placeholder.png)![A truck drives along a backroad, with electric poles and wires stretching across the landscape in Edmonton, Alberta](https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/48ab/live/18706a30-527f-11f0-ad6a-617a010885d7.jpg.webp)\n\n## Trucking's uneasy relationship with new tech\n\nMatching trucks with cargo has become digitised, adding efficiency, but driving down earnings.\n\n6 hrs ago](/news/articles/c5yeyn4gl80o)\n\n[![](https://static.files.bbci.co.uk/bbcdotcom/web/20250711-084946-a521911844-web-2.25.0-9/grey-placeholder.png)![A woman pushes a pram in front of a Wells Fargo bank branch](https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/a9c0/live/4f66b9f0-6629-11f0-af20-030418be2ca5.jpg.webp)\n\n## China blocks Wells Fargo banker from leaving due to 'criminal case'\n\nA foreign ministry spokesperson suggested the banker had breached Chinese law.\n\n16 hrs ago\n\nWorld](/news/articles/cn0q4q01yv4o)\n\n[![](https://static.files.bbci.co.uk/bbcdotcom/web/20250711-084946-a521911844-web-2.25.0-9/grey-placeholder.png)![A new grey-blue SUV sits in a blue display, in front of a large sign that reads \"Stellantis\", with smaller logos underneath for its car brands including Alfa Romeo, Chrysler, Jeep and Citroen.](https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/77bd/live/dc788b10-6611-11f0-af20-030418be2ca5.jpg.webp)\n\n## Car maker Stellantis says US tariffs have cost it ‚Ç¨300m\n\nThe company behind the brands V\n\n<error>Content truncated. Call the fetch tool with a start_index of 5000 to get more content.</error>",
